70/*
71 * Stability and versioning definitions. These #defines are used in the tables
72 * of identifiers below to fill in the attribute and version fields associated
73 * with each identifier. The DT_ATTR_* macros are a convenience to permit more
74 * concise declarations of common attributes such as Stable/Stable/Common. The
75 * DT_VERS_* macros declare the encoded integer values of all versions used so
76 * far. DT_VERS_LATEST must correspond to the latest version value among all
77 * versions exported by the D compiler. DT_VERS_STRING must be an ASCII string
78 * that contains DT_VERS_LATEST within it along with any suffixes (e.g. Beta).
79 * You must update DT_VERS_LATEST and DT_VERS_STRING when adding a new version,
80 * and then add the new version to the _dtrace_versions[] array declared below.
81 * Refer to the Solaris Dynamic Tracing Guide Stability and Versioning chapters
82 * respectively for an explanation of these DTrace features and their values.
83 *
84 * NOTE: Although the DTrace versioning scheme supports the labeling and
85 * introduction of incompatible changes (e.g. dropping an interface in a
86 * major release), the libdtrace code does not currently support this.
87 * All versions are assumed to strictly inherit from one another. If
88 * we ever need to provide divergent interfaces, this will need work.
89 */
90#define DT_ATTR_STABCMN { DTRACE_STABILITY_STABLE, \
91 DTRACE_STABILITY_STABLE, DTRACE_CLASS_COMMON }
92
93#define DT_ATTR_EVOLCMN { DTRACE_STABILITY_EVOLVING, \
94 DTRACE_STABILITY_EVOLVING, DTRACE_CLASS_COMMON \
95}
96
97/*
98 * The version number should be increased for every customer visible release
99 * of DTrace. The major number should be incremented when a fundamental
100 * change has been made that would affect all consumers, and would reflect
101 * sweeping changes to DTrace or the D language. The minor number should be
102 * incremented when a change is introduced that could break scripts that had
103 * previously worked; for example, adding a new built-in variable could break
104 * a script which was already using that identifier. The micro number should
105 * be changed when introducing functionality changes or major bug fixes that
106 * do not affect backward compatibility -- this is merely to make capabilities
107 * easily determined from the version number. Minor bugs do not require any
108 * modification to the version number.
109 */

111#define DT_VERS_1_1 DT_VERSION_NUMBER(1, 1, 0)

854static void
855dt_provmod_open(dt_provmod_t **provmod, dt_fdlist_t *dfp)
856{
857 dt_provmod_t *prov;
858 char path[PATH_MAX];
859 int fd;
860#ifdef illumos
861 struct dirent *dp, *ep;
862 DIR *dirp;
863
864 if ((dirp = opendir(_dtrace_provdir)) == NULL)
865 return; /* failed to open directory; just skip it */
866
867 ep = alloca(sizeof (struct dirent) + PATH_MAX + 1);
868 bzero(ep, sizeof (struct dirent) + PATH_MAX + 1);
869
870 while (readdir_r(dirp, ep, &dp) == 0 && dp != NULL) {
871 if (dp->d_name[0] == '.')
872 continue; /* skip "." and ".." */
873
874 if (dfp->df_ents == dfp->df_size) {
875 uint_t size = dfp->df_size ? dfp->df_size * 2 : 16;
876 int *fds = realloc(dfp->df_fds, size * sizeof (int));
877
878 if (fds == NULL)
879 break; /* skip the rest of this directory */
880
881 dfp->df_fds = fds;
882 dfp->df_size = size;
883 }
884
885 (void) snprintf(path, sizeof (path), "%s/%s",
886 _dtrace_provdir, dp->d_name);
887
888 if ((fd = open(path, O_RDONLY)) == -1)
889 continue; /* failed to open driver; just skip it */
890
891 if (((prov = malloc(sizeof (dt_provmod_t))) == NULL) ||
892 (prov->dp_name = malloc(strlen(dp->d_name) + 1)) == NULL) {
893 free(prov);
894 (void) close(fd);
895 break;
896 }
897
898 (void) strcpy(prov->dp_name, dp->d_name);
899 prov->dp_next = *provmod;
900 *provmod = prov;
901
902 dt_dprintf("opened provider %s\n", dp->d_name);
903 dfp->df_fds[dfp->df_ents++] = fd;
904 }
905
906 (void) closedir(dirp);
907#else /* !illumos */
908 char *p;
909 char *p1;
910 char *p_providers = NULL;
911 int error;
912 size_t len = 0;
913
914 /*
915 * Loop to allocate/reallocate memory for the string of provider
916 * names and retry:
917 */
918 while(1) {
919 /*
920 * The first time around, get the string length. The next time,
921 * hopefully we've allocated enough memory.
922 */
923 error = sysctlbyname("debug.dtrace.providers",p_providers,&len,NULL,0);
924 if (len == 0)
925 /* No providers? That's strange. Where's dtrace? */
926 break;
927 else if (error == 0 && p_providers == NULL) {
928 /*
929 * Allocate the initial memory which should be enough
930 * unless another provider loads before we have
931 * time to go back and get the string.
932 */
933 if ((p_providers = malloc(len)) == NULL)
934 /* How do we report errors here? */
935 return;
936 } else if (error == -1 && errno == ENOMEM) {
937 /*
938 * The current buffer isn't large enough, so
939 * reallocate it. We normally won't need to do this
940 * because providers aren't being loaded all the time.
941 */
942 if ((p = realloc(p_providers,len)) == NULL) {
943 free(p_providers);
944 /* How do we report errors here? */
945 return;
946 }
947 p_providers = p;
948 } else
949 break;
950 }
951
952 /* Check if we got a string of provider names: */
953 if (error == 0 && len > 0 && p_providers != NULL) {
954 p = p_providers;
955
956 /*
957 * Parse the string containing the space separated
958 * provider names.
959 */
960 while ((p1 = strsep(&p," ")) != NULL) {
961 if (dfp->df_ents == dfp->df_size) {
962 uint_t size = dfp->df_size ? dfp->df_size * 2 : 16;
963 int *fds = realloc(dfp->df_fds, size * sizeof (int));
964
965 if (fds == NULL)
966 break;
967
968 dfp->df_fds = fds;
969 dfp->df_size = size;
970 }
971
972 (void) snprintf(path, sizeof (path), "/dev/dtrace/%s", p1);
973
974 if ((fd = open(path, O_RDONLY)) == -1)
975 continue; /* failed to open driver; just skip it */
976
977 if (((prov = malloc(sizeof (dt_provmod_t))) == NULL) ||
978 (prov->dp_name = malloc(strlen(p1) + 1)) == NULL) {
979 free(prov);
980 (void) close(fd);
981 break;
982 }
983
984 (void) strcpy(prov->dp_name, p1);
985 prov->dp_next = *provmod;
986 *provmod = prov;
987
988 dt_dprintf("opened provider %s\n", p1);
989 dfp->df_fds[dfp->df_ents++] = fd;
990 }
991 }
992 if (p_providers != NULL)
993 free(p_providers);
994#endif /* illumos */
995}

997static void
998dt_provmod_destroy(dt_provmod_t **provmod)
999{
1000 dt_provmod_t *next, *current;
1001
1002 for (current = *provmod; current != NULL; current = next) {
1003 next = current->dp_next;
1004 free(current->dp_name);
1005 free(current);
1006 }
1007
1008 *provmod = NULL;
1009}

1058static dtrace_hdl_t *
1059dt_vopen(int version, int flags, int *errp,
1060 const dtrace_vector_t *vector, void *arg)
1061{
1062 dtrace_hdl_t *dtp = NULL;
1063 int dtfd = -1, ftfd = -1, fterr = 0;
1064 dtrace_prog_t *pgp;
1065 dt_module_t *dmp;
1066 dt_provmod_t *provmod = NULL;
1067 int i, err;
1068 struct rlimit rl;
1069
1070 const dt_intrinsic_t *dinp;
1071 const dt_typedef_t *dtyp;
1072 const dt_ident_t *idp;
1073
1074 dtrace_typeinfo_t dtt;
1075 ctf_funcinfo_t ctc;
1076 ctf_arinfo_t ctr;
1077
1078 dt_fdlist_t df = { NULL, 0, 0 };
1079
1080#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
1081 char isadef[32], utsdef[32];
1082 char s1[64], s2[64];
1083#endif
1084
1085 if (version <= 0)
1086 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EINVAL));
1087
1088 if (version > DTRACE_VERSION)
1089 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_VERSION));
1090
1091 if (version < DTRACE_VERSION) {
1092 /*
1093 * Currently, increasing the library version number is used to
1094 * denote a binary incompatible change. That is, a consumer
1095 * of the library cannot run on a version of the library with
1096 * a higher DTRACE_VERSION number than the consumer compiled
1097 * against. Once the library API has been committed to,
1098 * backwards binary compatibility will be required; at that
1099 * time, this check should change to return EDT_OVERSION only
1100 * if the specified version number is less than the version
1101 * number at the time of interface commitment.
1102 */
1103 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_OVERSION));
1104 }
1105
1106 if (flags & ~DTRACE_O_MASK)
1107 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EINVAL));
1108
1109 if ((flags & DTRACE_O_LP64) && (flags & DTRACE_O_ILP32))
1110 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EINVAL));
1111
1112 if (vector == NULL && arg != NULL)
1113 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EINVAL));
1114
1115 if (elf_version(EV_CURRENT) == EV_NONE)
1116 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_ELFVERSION));
1117
1118 if (vector != NULL || (flags & DTRACE_O_NODEV))
1119 goto alloc; /* do not attempt to open dtrace device */
1120
1121 /*
1122 * Before we get going, crank our limit on file descriptors up to the
1123 * hard limit. This is to allow for the fact that libproc keeps file
1124 * descriptors to objects open for the lifetime of the proc handle;
1125 * without raising our hard limit, we would have an acceptably small
1126 * bound on the number of processes that we could concurrently
1127 * instrument with the pid provider.
1128 */
1129 if (getrlimit(RLIMIT_NOFILE, &rl) == 0) {
1130 rl.rlim_cur = rl.rlim_max;
1131 (void) setrlimit(RLIMIT_NOFILE, &rl);
1132 }
1133
1134 /*
1135 * Get the device path of each of the providers. We hold them open
1136 * in the df.df_fds list until we open the DTrace driver itself,
1137 * allowing us to see all of the probes provided on this system. Once
1138 * we have the DTrace driver open, we can safely close all the providers
1139 * now that they have registered with the framework.
1140 */
1141 dt_provmod_open(&provmod, &df);
1142
1143 dtfd = open("/dev/dtrace/dtrace", O_RDWR);
1144 err = errno; /* save errno from opening dtfd */
1145#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
1146 /*
1147 * Automatically load the 'dtraceall' module if we couldn't open the
1148 * char device.
1149 */
1150 if (err == ENOENT && modfind("dtraceall") < 0) {
1151 kldload("dtraceall"); /* ignore the error */
1152 dtfd = open("/dev/dtrace/dtrace", O_RDWR);
1153 err = errno;
1154 }
1155#endif
1156#ifdef illumos
1157 ftfd = open("/dev/dtrace/provider/fasttrap", O_RDWR);
1158#else
1159 ftfd = open("/dev/dtrace/fasttrap", O_RDWR);
1160#endif
1161 fterr = ftfd == -1 ? errno : 0; /* save errno from open ftfd */
1162
1163 while (df.df_ents-- != 0)
1164 (void) close(df.df_fds[df.df_ents]);
1165
1166 free(df.df_fds);
1167
1168 /*
1169 * If we failed to open the dtrace device, fail dtrace_open().
1170 * We convert some kernel errnos to custom libdtrace errnos to
1171 * improve the resulting message from the usual strerror().
1172 */
1173 if (dtfd == -1) {
1174 dt_provmod_destroy(&provmod);
1175 switch (err) {
1176 case ENOENT:
1177 err = EDT_NOENT;
1178 break;
1179 case EBUSY:
1180 err = EDT_BUSY;
1181 break;
1182 case EACCES:
1183 err = EDT_ACCESS;
1184 break;
1185 }
1186 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, err));
1187 }
1188
1189 (void) fcntl(dtfd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
1190 (void) fcntl(ftfd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
1191
1192alloc:
1193 if ((dtp = malloc(sizeof (dtrace_hdl_t))) == NULL) {
1194 dt_provmod_destroy(&provmod);
1195 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1196 }
1197
1198 bzero(dtp, sizeof (dtrace_hdl_t));
1199 dtp->dt_oflags = flags;
1200#ifdef illumos
1201 dtp->dt_prcmode = DT_PROC_STOP_PREINIT;
1202#else
1203 dtp->dt_prcmode = DT_PROC_STOP_POSTINIT;
1204#endif
1205 dtp->dt_linkmode = DT_LINK_KERNEL;
1206 dtp->dt_linktype = DT_LTYP_ELF;
1207 dtp->dt_xlatemode = DT_XL_STATIC;
1208 dtp->dt_stdcmode = DT_STDC_XA;
1209 dtp->dt_encoding = DT_ENCODING_UNSET;
1210 dtp->dt_version = version;
1211 dtp->dt_fd = dtfd;
1212 dtp->dt_ftfd = ftfd;
1213 dtp->dt_fterr = fterr;
1214 dtp->dt_cdefs_fd = -1;
1215 dtp->dt_ddefs_fd = -1;
1216#ifdef illumos
1217 dtp->dt_stdout_fd = -1;
1218#else
1219 dtp->dt_freopen_fp = NULL;
1220#endif
1221 dtp->dt_modbuckets = _dtrace_strbuckets;
1222 dtp->dt_mods = calloc(dtp->dt_modbuckets, sizeof (dt_module_t *));
1223#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1224 dtp->dt_kmods = calloc(dtp->dt_modbuckets, sizeof (dt_module_t *));
1225#endif
1226 dtp->dt_provbuckets = _dtrace_strbuckets;
1227 dtp->dt_provs = calloc(dtp->dt_provbuckets, sizeof (dt_provider_t *));
1228 dt_proc_hash_create(dtp);
1229 dtp->dt_vmax = DT_VERS_LATEST;
1230 dtp->dt_cpp_path = NULL;
1231 for (i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(_dtrace_defcpps) / sizeof(_dtrace_defcpps[0]); ++i) {
1232 if (access(_dtrace_defcpps[i], X_OK) == 0) {
1233 dtp->dt_cpp_path = strdup(_dtrace_defcpps[i]);
1234 break;
1235 }
1236 }
1237 if (dtp->dt_cpp_path == NULL)
1238 dtp->dt_cpp_path = strdup("cpp");
1239
1240 dtp->dt_cpp_argv = malloc(sizeof (char *));
1241 dtp->dt_cpp_argc = 1;
1242 dtp->dt_cpp_args = 1;
1243 dtp->dt_ld_path = strdup(_dtrace_defld);
1244#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1245 dtp->dt_objcopy_path = strdup(_dtrace_defobjcopy);
1246#endif
1247 dtp->dt_provmod = provmod;
1248 dtp->dt_vector = vector;
1249 dtp->dt_varg = arg;
1250 dt_dof_init(dtp);
1251 (void) uname(&dtp->dt_uts);
1252
1253 if (dtp->dt_mods == NULL || dtp->dt_provs == NULL ||
1254 dtp->dt_procs == NULL || dtp->dt_ld_path == NULL ||
1255#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1256 dtp->dt_kmods == NULL ||
1257 dtp->dt_objcopy_path == NULL ||
1258#endif
1259 dtp->dt_cpp_path == NULL || dtp->dt_cpp_argv == NULL)
1260 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1261
1262 for (i = 0; i < DTRACEOPT_MAX; i++)
1263 dtp->dt_options[i] = DTRACEOPT_UNSET;
1264
1265 dtp->dt_cpp_argv[0] = (char *)strbasename(dtp->dt_cpp_path);
1266
1267#ifdef illumos
1268 (void) snprintf(isadef, sizeof (isadef), "-D__SUNW_D_%u",
1269 (uint_t)(sizeof (void *) * NBBY));
1270
1271 (void) snprintf(utsdef, sizeof (utsdef), "-D__%s_%s",
1272 dt_get_sysinfo(SI_SYSNAME, s1, sizeof (s1)),
1273 dt_get_sysinfo(SI_RELEASE, s2, sizeof (s2)));
1274
1275 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__sun") == NULL ||
1276 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__unix") == NULL ||
1277 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__SVR4") == NULL ||
1278 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__SUNW_D=1") == NULL ||
1279 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, isadef) == NULL ||
1280 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, utsdef) == NULL)
1281 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1282#endif
1283
1284 if (flags & DTRACE_O_NODEV)
1285 bcopy(&_dtrace_conf, &dtp->dt_conf, sizeof (_dtrace_conf));
1286 else if (dt_ioctl(dtp, DTRACEIOC_CONF, &dtp->dt_conf) != 0)
1287 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, errno));
1288
1289 if (flags & DTRACE_O_LP64)
1290 dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel = CTF_MODEL_LP64;
1291 else if (flags & DTRACE_O_ILP32)
1292 dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel = CTF_MODEL_ILP32;
1293
1294#ifdef __sparc
1295 /*
1296 * On SPARC systems, __sparc is always defined for <sys/isa_defs.h>
1297 * and __sparcv9 is defined if we are doing a 64-bit compile.
1298 */
1299 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__sparc") == NULL)
1300 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1301
1302 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel == CTF_MODEL_LP64 &&
1303 dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__sparcv9") == NULL)
1304 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1305#endif
1306
1307#ifdef illumos
1308#ifdef __x86
1309 /*
1310 * On x86 systems, __i386 is defined for <sys/isa_defs.h> for 32-bit
1311 * compiles and __amd64 is defined for 64-bit compiles. Unlike SPARC,
1312 * they are defined exclusive of one another (see PSARC 2004/619).
1313 */
1314 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel == CTF_MODEL_LP64) {
1315 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__amd64") == NULL)
1316 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1317 } else {
1318 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-D__i386") == NULL)
1319 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1320 }
1321#endif
1322#else
1323#if defined(__amd64__) || defined(__i386__)
1324 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel == CTF_MODEL_LP64) {
1325 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-m64") == NULL)
1326 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1327 } else {
1328 if (dt_cpp_add_arg(dtp, "-m32") == NULL)
1329 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1330 }
1331#endif
1332#endif
1333
1334 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_difversion < DIF_VERSION)
1335 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_DIFVERS));
1336
1337 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel == CTF_MODEL_ILP32)
1338 bcopy(_dtrace_ints_32, dtp->dt_ints, sizeof (_dtrace_ints_32));
1339 else
1340 bcopy(_dtrace_ints_64, dtp->dt_ints, sizeof (_dtrace_ints_64));
1341
1342 /*
1343 * On FreeBSD the kernel module name can't be hard-coded. The
1344 * 'kern.bootfile' sysctl value tells us exactly which file is being
1345 * used as the kernel.
1346 */
1347#ifndef illumos
1348# ifdef __FreeBSD__
1349# define THREAD "struct thread"
1350# define MUTEX "struct mtx"
1351# define RWLOCK "struct rwlock"
1352# endif
1353# ifdef __NetBSD__
1354# define THREAD "struct lwp"
1355# define MUTEX "struct kmutex"
1356# define RWLOCK "struct krwlock"
1357# endif
1358 {
1359 const char *p;
1360 char kernname[512];
1361
1362 p = dt_bootfile(kernname, sizeof(kernname));
1363
1364 /*
1365 * Format the global variables based on the kernel module name.
1366 */
1367 snprintf(curthread_str, sizeof(curthread_str), "%s`%s *", p, THREAD);
1368 snprintf(intmtx_str, sizeof(intmtx_str), "int(%s`%s *)", p, MUTEX);
1369 snprintf(threadmtx_str, sizeof(threadmtx_str), "%s *(%s`%s *)",
1370 THREAD, p, MUTEX);
1371 snprintf(rwlock_str, sizeof(rwlock_str), "int(%s`%s *)", p, RWLOCK);
1372 snprintf(sxlock_str, sizeof(sxlock_str), "int(%s`struct sxlock *)", p);
1373 }
1374# undef THREAD
1375# undef MUTEX
1376# undef RWLOCK
1377#endif
1378
1379 dtp->dt_macros = dt_idhash_create("macro", NULL, 0, UINT_MAX);
1380 dtp->dt_aggs = dt_idhash_create("aggregation", NULL,
1381 DTRACE_AGGVARIDNONE + 1, UINT_MAX);
1382
1383 dtp->dt_globals = dt_idhash_create("global", _dtrace_globals,
1384 DIF_VAR_OTHER_UBASE, DIF_VAR_OTHER_MAX);
1385
1386 dtp->dt_tls = dt_idhash_create("thread local", NULL,
1387 DIF_VAR_OTHER_UBASE, DIF_VAR_OTHER_MAX);
1388
1389 if (dtp->dt_macros == NULL || dtp->dt_aggs == NULL ||
1390 dtp->dt_globals == NULL || dtp->dt_tls == NULL)
1391 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1392
1393 /*
1394 * Populate the dt_macros identifier hash table by hand: we can't use
1395 * the dt_idhash_populate() mechanism because we're not yet compiling
1396 * and dtrace_update() needs to immediately reference these idents.
1397 */
1398 for (idp = _dtrace_macros; idp->di_name != NULL; idp++) {
1399 if (dt_idhash_insert(dtp->dt_macros, idp->di_name,
1400 idp->di_kind, idp->di_flags, idp->di_id, idp->di_attr,
1401 idp->di_vers, idp->di_ops ? idp->di_ops : &dt_idops_thaw,
1402 idp->di_iarg, 0) == NULL)
1403 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1404 }
1405
1406 /*
1407 * Update the module list using /system/object and load the values for
1408 * the macro variable definitions according to the current process.
1409 */
1410 dtrace_update(dtp);
1411
1412 /*
1413 * Select the intrinsics and typedefs we want based on the data model.
1414 * The intrinsics are under "C". The typedefs are added under "D".
1415 */
1416 if (dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel == CTF_MODEL_ILP32) {
1417 dinp = _dtrace_intrinsics_32;
1418 dtyp = _dtrace_typedefs_32;
1419 } else {
1420 dinp = _dtrace_intrinsics_64;
1421 dtyp = _dtrace_typedefs_64;
1422 }
1423
1424 /*
1425 * Create a dynamic CTF container under the "C" scope for intrinsic
1426 * types and types defined in ANSI-C header files that are included.
1427 */
1428 if ((dmp = dtp->dt_cdefs = dt_module_create(dtp, "C")) == NULL)
1429 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1430
1431 if ((dmp->dm_ctfp = ctf_create(&dtp->dt_ctferr)) == NULL)
1432 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1433
1434 dt_dprintf("created CTF container for %s (%p)\n",
1435 dmp->dm_name, (void *)dmp->dm_ctfp);
1436
1437 (void) ctf_setmodel(dmp->dm_ctfp, dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel);
1438 ctf_setspecific(dmp->dm_ctfp, dmp);
1439
1440 dmp->dm_flags = DT_DM_LOADED; /* fake up loaded bit */
1441 dmp->dm_modid = -1; /* no module ID */
1442
1443 /*
1444 * Fill the dynamic "C" CTF container with all of the intrinsic
1445 * integer and floating-point types appropriate for this data model.
1446 */
1447 for (; dinp->din_name != NULL; dinp++) {
1448 if (dinp->din_kind == CTF_K_INTEGER) {
1449 err = ctf_add_integer(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1450 dinp->din_name, &dinp->din_data);
1451 } else {
1452 err = ctf_add_float(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1453 dinp->din_name, &dinp->din_data);
1454 }
1455
1456 if (err == CTF_ERR) {
1457 dt_dprintf("failed to add %s to C container: %s\n",
1458 dinp->din_name, ctf_errmsg(
1459 ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1460 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 if (ctf_update(dmp->dm_ctfp) != 0) {
1465 dt_dprintf("failed to update C container: %s\n",
1466 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1467 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1468 }
1469
1470 /*
1471 * Add intrinsic pointer types that are needed to initialize printf
1472 * format dictionary types (see table in dt_printf.c).
1473 */
1474 (void) ctf_add_pointer(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1475 ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "void"));
1476
1477 (void) ctf_add_pointer(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1478 ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "char"));
1479
1480 (void) ctf_add_pointer(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1481 ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "int"));
1482
1483 if (ctf_update(dmp->dm_ctfp) != 0) {
1484 dt_dprintf("failed to update C container: %s\n",
1485 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1486 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1487 }
1488
1489 /*
1490 * Create a dynamic CTF container under the "D" scope for types that
1491 * are defined by the D program itself or on-the-fly by the D compiler.
1492 * The "D" CTF container is a child of the "C" CTF container.
1493 */
1494 if ((dmp = dtp->dt_ddefs = dt_module_create(dtp, "D")) == NULL)
1495 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_NOMEM));
1496
1497 if ((dmp->dm_ctfp = ctf_create(&dtp->dt_ctferr)) == NULL)
1498 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1499
1500 dt_dprintf("created CTF container for %s (%p)\n",
1501 dmp->dm_name, (void *)dmp->dm_ctfp);
1502
1503 (void) ctf_setmodel(dmp->dm_ctfp, dtp->dt_conf.dtc_ctfmodel);
1504 ctf_setspecific(dmp->dm_ctfp, dmp);
1505
1506 dmp->dm_flags = DT_DM_LOADED; /* fake up loaded bit */
1507 dmp->dm_modid = -1; /* no module ID */
1508
1509 if (ctf_import(dmp->dm_ctfp, dtp->dt_cdefs->dm_ctfp) == CTF_ERR) {
1510 dt_dprintf("failed to import D parent container: %s\n",
1511 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1512 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1513 }
1514
1515 /*
1516 * Fill the dynamic "D" CTF container with all of the built-in typedefs
1517 * that we need to use for our D variable and function definitions.
1518 * This ensures that basic inttypes.h names are always available to us.
1519 */
1520 for (; dtyp->dty_src != NULL; dtyp++) {
1521 if (ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1522 dtyp->dty_dst, ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp,
1523 dtyp->dty_src)) == CTF_ERR) {
1524 dt_dprintf("failed to add typedef %s %s to D "
1525 "container: %s", dtyp->dty_src, dtyp->dty_dst,
1526 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1527 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1528 }
1529 }
1530
1531 /*
1532 * Insert a CTF ID corresponding to a pointer to a type of kind
1533 * CTF_K_FUNCTION we can use in the compiler for function pointers.
1534 * CTF treats all function pointers as "int (*)()" so we only need one.
1535 */
1536 ctc.ctc_return = ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "int");
1537 ctc.ctc_argc = 0;
1538 ctc.ctc_flags = 0;
1539
1540 dtp->dt_type_func = ctf_add_function(dmp->dm_ctfp,
1541 CTF_ADD_ROOT, &ctc, NULL);
1542
1543 dtp->dt_type_fptr = ctf_add_pointer(dmp->dm_ctfp,
1544 CTF_ADD_ROOT, dtp->dt_type_func);
1545
1546 /*
1547 * We also insert CTF definitions for the special D intrinsic types
1548 * string and <DYN> into the D container. The string type is added
1549 * as a typedef of char[n]. The <DYN> type is an alias for void.
1550 * We compare types to these special CTF ids throughout the compiler.
1551 */
1552 ctr.ctr_contents = ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "char");
1553 ctr.ctr_index = ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "long");
1554 ctr.ctr_nelems = _dtrace_strsize;
1555
1556 dtp->dt_type_str = ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1557 "string", ctf_add_array(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT, &ctr));
1558
1559 dtp->dt_type_dyn = ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1560 "<DYN>", ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "void"));
1561
1562 dtp->dt_type_stack = ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1563 "stack", ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "void"));
1564
1565 dtp->dt_type_symaddr = ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1566 "_symaddr", ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "void"));
1567
1568 dtp->dt_type_usymaddr = ctf_add_typedef(dmp->dm_ctfp, CTF_ADD_ROOT,
1569 "_usymaddr", ctf_lookup_by_name(dmp->dm_ctfp, "void"));
1570
1571 if (dtp->dt_type_func == CTF_ERR || dtp->dt_type_fptr == CTF_ERR ||
1572 dtp->dt_type_str == CTF_ERR || dtp->dt_type_dyn == CTF_ERR ||
1573 dtp->dt_type_stack == CTF_ERR || dtp->dt_type_symaddr == CTF_ERR ||
1574 dtp->dt_type_usymaddr == CTF_ERR) {
1575 dt_dprintf("failed to add intrinsic to D container: %s\n",
1576 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1577 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1578 }
1579
1580 if (ctf_update(dmp->dm_ctfp) != 0) {
1581 dt_dprintf("failed update D container: %s\n",
1582 ctf_errmsg(ctf_errno(dmp->dm_ctfp)));
1583 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_CTF));
1584 }
1585
1586 /*
1587 * Initialize the integer description table used to convert integer
1588 * constants to the appropriate types. Refer to the comments above
1589 * dt_node_int() for a complete description of how this table is used.
1590 */
1591 for (i = 0; i < sizeof (dtp->dt_ints) / sizeof (dtp->dt_ints[0]); i++) {
1592 if (dtrace_lookup_by_type(dtp, DTRACE_OBJ_EVERY,
1593 dtp->dt_ints[i].did_name, &dtt) != 0) {
1594 dt_dprintf("failed to lookup integer type %s: %s\n",
1595 dtp->dt_ints[i].did_name,
1596 dtrace_errmsg(dtp, dtrace_errno(dtp)));
1597 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, dtp->dt_errno));
1598 }
1599 dtp->dt_ints[i].did_ctfp = dtt.dtt_ctfp;
1600 dtp->dt_ints[i].did_type = dtt.dtt_type;
1601 }
1602
1603 /*
1604 * Now that we've created the "C" and "D" containers, move them to the
1605 * start of the module list so that these types and symbols are found
1606 * first (for stability) when iterating through the module list.
1607 */
1608 dt_list_delete(&dtp->dt_modlist, dtp->dt_ddefs);
1609 dt_list_prepend(&dtp->dt_modlist, dtp->dt_ddefs);
1610
1611 dt_list_delete(&dtp->dt_modlist, dtp->dt_cdefs);
1612 dt_list_prepend(&dtp->dt_modlist, dtp->dt_cdefs);
1613
1614 if (dt_pfdict_create(dtp) == -1)
1615 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, dtp->dt_errno));
1616
1617 /*
1618 * If we are opening libdtrace DTRACE_O_NODEV enable C_ZDEFS by default
1619 * because without /dev/dtrace open, we will not be able to load the
1620 * names and attributes of any providers or probes from the kernel.
1621 */
1622 if (flags & DTRACE_O_NODEV)
1623 dtp->dt_cflags |= DTRACE_C_ZDEFS;
1624
1625 /*
1626 * Load hard-wired inlines into the definition cache by calling the
1627 * compiler on the raw definition string defined above.
1628 */
1629 if ((pgp = dtrace_program_strcompile(dtp, _dtrace_hardwire,
1630 DTRACE_PROBESPEC_NONE, DTRACE_C_EMPTY, 0, NULL)) == NULL) {
1631 dt_dprintf("failed to load hard-wired definitions: %s\n",
1632 dtrace_errmsg(dtp, dtrace_errno(dtp)));
1633 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, EDT_HARDWIRE));
1634 }
1635
1636 dt_program_destroy(dtp, pgp);
1637
1638 /*
1639 * Set up the default DTrace library path. Once set, the next call to
1640 * dt_compile() will compile all the libraries. We intentionally defer
1641 * library processing to improve overhead for clients that don't ever
1642 * compile, and to provide better error reporting (because the full
1643 * reporting of compiler errors requires dtrace_open() to succeed).
1644 */
1645#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1646#ifdef __LP64__
1647 if ((dtp->dt_oflags & DTRACE_O_ILP32) != 0) {
1648 if (dtrace_setopt(dtp, "libdir", _dtrace_libdir32) != 0)
1649 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, dtp->dt_errno));
1650 }
1651#endif
1652 if (dtrace_setopt(dtp, "libdir", _dtrace_libdir) != 0)
1653 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, dtp->dt_errno));
1654#else
1655 if (dtrace_setopt(dtp, "libdir", _dtrace_libdir) != 0)
1656 return (set_open_errno(dtp, errp, dtp->dt_errno));
1657#endif
1658
1659 return (dtp);
1660}

1675void
1676dtrace_close(dtrace_hdl_t *dtp)
1677{
1678 dt_ident_t *idp, *ndp;
1679 dt_module_t *dmp;
1680 dt_provider_t *pvp;
1681 dtrace_prog_t *pgp;
1682 dt_xlator_t *dxp;
1683 dt_dirpath_t *dirp;
1684#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1685 dt_kmodule_t *dkm;
1686 uint_t h;
1687#endif
1688 int i;
1689
1690 if (dtp->dt_procs != NULL)
1691 dt_proc_hash_destroy(dtp);
1692
1693 while ((pgp = dt_list_next(&dtp->dt_programs)) != NULL)
1694 dt_program_destroy(dtp, pgp);
1695
1696 while ((dxp = dt_list_next(&dtp->dt_xlators)) != NULL)
1697 dt_xlator_destroy(dtp, dxp);
1698
1699 dt_free(dtp, dtp->dt_xlatormap);
1700
1701 for (idp = dtp->dt_externs; idp != NULL; idp = ndp) {
1702 ndp = idp->di_next;
1703 dt_ident_destroy(idp);
1704 }
1705
1706 if (dtp->dt_macros != NULL)
1707 dt_idhash_destroy(dtp->dt_macros);
1708 if (dtp->dt_aggs != NULL)
1709 dt_idhash_destroy(dtp->dt_aggs);
1710 if (dtp->dt_globals != NULL)
1711 dt_idhash_destroy(dtp->dt_globals);
1712 if (dtp->dt_tls != NULL)
1713 dt_idhash_destroy(dtp->dt_tls);
1714
1715#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1716 for (h = 0; h < dtp->dt_modbuckets; h++)
1717 while ((dkm = dtp->dt_kmods[h]) != NULL) {
1718 dtp->dt_kmods[h] = dkm->dkm_next;
1719 free(dkm->dkm_name);
1720 free(dkm);
1721 }
1722#endif
1723
1724 while ((dmp = dt_list_next(&dtp->dt_modlist)) != NULL)
1725 dt_module_destroy(dtp, dmp);
1726
1727 while ((pvp = dt_list_next(&dtp->dt_provlist)) != NULL)
1728 dt_provider_destroy(dtp, pvp);
1729
1730 if (dtp->dt_fd != -1)
1731 (void) close(dtp->dt_fd);
1732 if (dtp->dt_ftfd != -1)
1733 (void) close(dtp->dt_ftfd);
1734 if (dtp->dt_cdefs_fd != -1)
1735 (void) close(dtp->dt_cdefs_fd);
1736 if (dtp->dt_ddefs_fd != -1)
1737 (void) close(dtp->dt_ddefs_fd);
1738#ifdef illumos
1739 if (dtp->dt_stdout_fd != -1)
1740 (void) close(dtp->dt_stdout_fd);
1741#else
1742 if (dtp->dt_freopen_fp != NULL)
1743 (void) fclose(dtp->dt_freopen_fp);
1744#endif
1745
1746 dt_epid_destroy(dtp);
1747 dt_aggid_destroy(dtp);
1748 dt_format_destroy(dtp);
1749 dt_strdata_destroy(dtp);
1750 dt_buffered_destroy(dtp);
1751 dt_aggregate_destroy(dtp);
1752 dt_pfdict_destroy(dtp);
1753 dt_provmod_destroy(&dtp->dt_provmod);
1754 dt_dof_fini(dtp);
1755
1756 for (i = 1; i < dtp->dt_cpp_argc; i++)
1757 free(dtp->dt_cpp_argv[i]);
1758
1759 while ((dirp = dt_list_next(&dtp->dt_lib_path)) != NULL) {
1760 dt_list_delete(&dtp->dt_lib_path, dirp);
1761 free(dirp->dir_path);
1762 free(dirp);
1763 }
1764
1765 free(dtp->dt_cpp_argv);
1766 free(dtp->dt_cpp_path);
1767 free(dtp->dt_ld_path);
1768#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1769 free(dtp->dt_objcopy_path);
1770#endif
1771
1772 free(dtp->dt_mods);
1773#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__)
1774 free(dtp->dt_kmods);
1775#endif
1776 free(dtp->dt_provs);
1777 free(dtp);
1778}
